<section version="5.0" xml:lang="en" xml:id="tools-3rd-party-tools" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
<title>3rd Party Tools</title>
<section xml:id="section-954928396024079">
<title>Maven JAXB Plugin</title>
<para>The 
    <link xlink:href="http://maven-jaxb2-plugin.java.net/">Maven2 plugin for
    JAXB2</link> is hosted at java.net. If you are using Maven, JAXB
    jars are available in 
    <link xlink:href="https://maven.java.net/content/repositories/releases/">the java.net maven
    repository</link>. This repository is synced with maven central, so usually you find all JAXB releases in maven central after ~ 1 day after java.net release.</para>
</section>
<section xml:id="section-2873137906334116">
<title>JAXB Workshop</title>
<para>
    <link xlink:href="http://jaxb-workshop.java.net/">JAXB Workshop</link>
    hosts a collection of visual tools and IDE plugins useful for
    working with JAXB.</para>
</section>
<section xml:id="section-2642114715432213">
<title>XJC Plugins</title>
<para>Various people in the community have developed plugins for
    XJC that you can use today. These plugins allow you to
    enhance/alter the code generation of XJC in many different
    ways. See 
    <link xlink:href="http://jaxb2-commons.java.net/">the list of
    plugins</link> (if you are interested in hosting your plugin here,
    let us know.)</para>
</section>
<section xml:id="section-926973453240119">
<title>RDBMS Persistence</title>
<para>Lexi has developed the 
    <link xlink:href="http://confluence.highsource.org/display/HJ3/Home">HyperJAXB3
    project</link> for RDBMS persistence support for the JAXB RI. </para>
</section>
</section>
